Directory structure:

  dir/
    raw/
      XXX.jpg	  original image, will not be touched
    large/
      NNNN.html	  image page
      XXX.jpg	  Copy of original (possibly rotated)
    medium/
      NNNN.html	  image page
      XXX.jpg	  generated from large/XXX.jpg
    thumbnails/
      XXX.jpg	  generated from large/XXX.jpg
    images/	  images for buttons
    index.html	  first (or only) index page
    indexN.html	  other index pages
    info.dat	  control data
    .cache	  image information cache

Process:

  Process info.dat, if it exists.
  Copy or copy/rotate	from <raw>    to <large> unless it exists.
  Generate <medium>	from <large>		 unless it exists.
  Generate <thumbnails> from <large>		 unless it exists.
  Generate image pages.
  Generate index pages.

Notes:

  <dir> defaults to current directory unless specified with --dest option.
  <raw> may be specified with --source option (e.g., to copy from CD).
  An alternate info.dat can be specified with --info option.
  "unless it exists" will be ignored with --clobber option.
  With no <raw>, the <large> is taken as source, and rotation is disabled.

Format of Control/Info file:

  #-lines and empty lines are ignored.

  Lines starting with ! indicate settings

    !title XXX	     set the title to XXX, override with --title
    !page NxM	     set the layout to N rows (--rows) and 
		     M columns (--columns)
    !thumbsize NNN   desired width of thumbnails (--thumbsize)
    !mediumsize NNN  desired width of medium sized images (--mediumsize)
    !tag	     tagline for all following images
    !caption	     caption code for index pages (--caption)
		     a sequence of f (file name), s (WxH),
		     c (caption), t (tag line); default "fct".

  Other lines contain image info:

    XXX.jpg [ -O:n ] [ caption ]
      -O:n controls orientation (n x 90 degrees)

    If the image name contains a directory, multi mode is enabled.

    If the name is "*", all files found in the source directory are
    processed. 
